# Professional README Generator

![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-brightgreen)

## Description

I wanted to provide an easier way to create a README file without having to copy and paste from an online format. I built this application so that all future projects would have a more polished README file and follow the same structure and format for each one. Being able to use this generator will allow me to create a README file without having to find an example online and modify it's content. I learned quite a bit about node modules, specifically the inquirer package, and how it can be used to create many different prompts for more detailed questions and answers.  I also learned how to export/import functions to seperate file components and allow for smaller and cleaner code. Using multiple javascript files and linking them together allows for more seperation of concerns when working with a team on future applications and projects.

