## Installation

-You will need to initialize the npm package by running npm init in the terminal. Once institialized, you can then install the package by running npm i in the terminal. Finally, you want to make sure to have the inquirer version 8.2.4 installed by running npm i inquirer@version8.2.4. After all these are installed you should be able to invoke the application by running node index.js in the terminal.

## Usage

Usage of this application is fairly straight forward. Once you initialize the program, you can navigate through each prompt by providing answers to the corresponding questions. If you are presented with a prompt asking for a section that you do not wish to add to the readme, just respond no to the prompt and it will not include a response for that section in the README file. Make sure to include correct filepaths for any URL or filepath requests, or it will return a broken image or link in the markdown text and require correction later on.

[Profeesional README Generator Walkthrough](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1b75ohsouGyAumwdFEn184B-vS8Xxx7TE/view)

